title: Fire guts Mount Isa Police beat shopfront
text:
Topix › Pacific Travel › Fire guts Mount Isa Police beat shopf... Fire guts Mount Isa Police beat shopfront 8 hrs ago Read more: Sydney Morning Herald 
Firefighters believe a police shopfront in the north west Queensland town of Mount Isa was deliberately torched in the early hours of Saturday morning. A number of emergency calls reported the police beat at Pioneer, in the town's inner east, was ablaze, with several reporting hearing explosions about 1.45am.
